Keith Szarabajka https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Keith_Szarabajka 0 Keith Szarabajka (; Polish: [ʂaraˈbajka]; born December 2, 1952) is an American actor and voice actor known as Mickey Kostmayer in The Equalizer, Daniel Holtz in Angel, Harlan Williams in Golden Years, Trigon on Teen Titans, and Gerard Stephens in The Dark Knight. He is also known for portraying Detective Herschel Biggs in the 2011 crime thriller video game L.A. Noire, which included his likeness.
